Introduction

IRRIS (I is the Reflection of Reality and Illusions) was a girl group managed by Justice Records, a subsidiary of Taewon Entertainment and Mellow Entertainment.

The group originally debuted with the name REDSQUARE in 2020 under About Entertainment, and eventually Iconic MNE. Two years after debuting, the agency announced that the group would undergo re-branding. On June 10, 2022, it was announced that the group would be changing their name to IRRIS.

IRRIS is composed of four members: I.L, Nina, Yunseul, and Liv. The 3 members of IRRIS are previous members of REDSQUARE—I.L. as Green, Yunseul as Ari, and Liv as ChaeA. The two previous members of REDSQUARE, Lina and Bomin, were confirmed to not be joining the group.

On June 20, 2022, IRRIS announced they would make their debut with a mini-album titled "Wanna Know" which would be released on July 06, 2022. In May of 2024, Liv shared with a fan on social media that the group's current state is unknown.
